<title>PERU: Peru hikes minimum private sector wage to $100/mo.</title>
<headline>Peru hikes minimum private sector wage to $100/mo.</headline>
<dateline>LIMA 1997-04-01</dateline>
<text>
<p>The Peruvian government decreed Tuesday a 23 percent hike in nominal terms of the minimum private sector wage to a monthly 265 soles ($100) from 215 soles ($81) previously.</p>
<p>According to an &quot;urgent&quot; decree in the government daily El Peruano, the new daily minimum wage in the private sector is equivalent to a daily 8.83 soles ($3.33).</p>
<p>The decree did not lay out any reason for the increase.</p>
<p>((-- Lima newsroom, 511 221-2134))</p>
